The First is, 1 Cor. 5.1. 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 , which is interpreted, Fornication is reported commonly among you:
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 is here translated, commonly, ordinarily, or frequently; and it can have no other sense; For if it should be translated here by the word at all, it would be sound without sense. If I may take the liberty then to translate it so in the Text you have alleadged, then it will run thus, Swear not commonly, ordinarily, or frequently;
and you see I have good Authority for what I have done.
